Nutrition & Hydration

To ensure that every greyhound receives the food and water neede for optimal development, health and wellbeing

Standards

Food

  1. All greyhounds must be fed at least once daily. Food must be provided in sufficient quantity and nutritional quality. Food must be canine-appropriate and meet the daily requirements for the greyhound’s age, size, condition, and level of activity. R

Food

  1. All greyhounds must be fed at least once daily. Food must be provided in sufficient quantity and nutritional quality. Food must be canine-appropriate and meet the daily requirements for the greyhound’s age, size, condition, and level of activity. R

Note: Participants who keep retired greyhouds ar required to comply with those Standards marked with an "R" in relation to those greyhounds.
